The magnetic helical black brane solution is described by the existence of a function $b(z) \neq 0$. As described in appendix \ref{sec:DhokerKraus}, in the limiting case $b(z) = 0$, one obtains the electrically charged Reissner-Nordstroem black brane with $\bar{B}=0$ or the electrically and magnetically charged brane for $\bar{B} \neq 0$. The boundary between the two regimes is therefore naturally defined as the region for which $b(z) \approx 0$.\footnote{Numerically, the boundary is characterised by $b_2 \approx 10^{-9}$ as introduced in \eqref{eq:Exp_metric_AdS}, see discussion in appendix \ref{sec:NumDetail}.}

