Fig.~\ref{fig:gamma15_Error} displays the error for the configurations mentioned in the previous section. The left panel shows the case $\bar{B}=0$ and we see the typical exponential convergence provided by the spectral method. The right panel depicts the case $\bar{B}=0.275$. Despite the presence of logarithmic terms, the convergence rate is very efficient and we do not observe a significant influence of an algebraic decay within the machine limits imposed by round off errors. 

